# File Manager CLI

A command-line File Manager built with Python following Clean Architecture principles using JSON persistence

## Features

✅ Create files

✅ Read file content

✅ Modify file content

✅ Delete files

✅ List all files

---

# Supported File Types

The application supports extensions like:

- txt
- pdf
- docx
- ppt
- py
- js


---

# Project Structure

```text
src/
│
├── entities/
│   └── file.py
│
├──use_cases/
│   ├─create_file.py
│   ├─read_file.py
│   ├─delete_file.py
│   ├─list_files.py
│   ├─modify_file.py
│   └──interfaces/
│       └──file_repository.py
│
│
├── interface_adapters/
│   ├── controller/file_controller.py
│   ├── presenter/file_presenter.py
│   └── repository/in_memory_file_repository.py
│
│
├── frameworks_and_drivers/
│   └── cli.py
│
└── main.py
```

---

# Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
```

Go to the project folder:

```bash
cd CLI-Tool_pet.project
```

---

# Run the Application

Display help:

```bash
py main.py -h
```

---

# Commands

## Create a File

```bash
py main.py create-file --name hello.txt --content "Hello World"
```

Example output:

```text
✓ file has been created successfully
```

## Read a File

```bash
py main.py read-file --name hello.txt
```

## Modify a File

```bash
py main.py modify-file --name hello.txt --content "Updated content"
```

## Delete a File

```bash
py main.py delete-file --name hello.txt
```

## List Files

```bash
py main.py list-files
```

---

# Data Storage

Files are stored inside:

```text
data/files.json
```

